Alex wrote:

&gt; Hi St.Ack,
&gt;
&gt; Well, we need to restablish state if the crawl fails, and the only way to
&gt; keep the state is using the checkpoint feature.  We would definitely 
&gt; want to
&gt; run this in the background within the same job.  Is it possible to 
&gt; save the
&gt; checkpoint in a processor call (obviously not being paused) w/out 
&gt; problems?

Crawler must be quiescent before you checkpoint.  Otherwise the 
checkpoint will be inconsistent.  So, at least for now until we do more 
work, the pause is required.

If you want to have the checkpointing task run in same process, a 
processor is probably not the right place to launch a background 
checkpointing task from.  Better to subclass 
org.archive.crawler.Heritrix and in your subclass launch the background 
thread that does pause, watch for quiescent heritrix (i.e. Heritrix is 
PAUSED), checkpoint, watch for end-of-checkpoint, resume, all on a 
schedule or, write your own little launcher programer that does 
something like following pseudocode adding in your backgrounded 
checkpointing thread:

Heritrix h = new Heritrix();
Thread bkrdchkptr = new CheckpointerThread(h);
bkrdchkptr.setDaemon(true);
h.addJob(&quot;/path/to/jar/of/orderfile&quot;);
h.startCrawling();
bkrdchkptr.start();

Then in  your bkgrdchkptr thread run method, do stuff like:

run() {

    .....
          wait(LONG_TIME);
          if (h.isCawling()) {
              h.pause();
              while(h.getStatus() != &quot;PAUSED&quot;) {
                  h.checkpoint();
                  while(h.getState() != &quot;PAUSED&quot;) {
                      h.resume();
                  }
              }
          }
    .....
}


We can help out with the &quot;pause, watch for quiescent heritrix....etc.&quot; 
bit because we need to add this into the crawler anyways. Maybe you can 
make a patch for a 
checkpoint-on-a-very-basic-schedule-set-in-heritrix-properties feature 
and we&#39;ll just add it to the crawler?


But first, I&#39;d suggest that you play some with checkpointing first 
manually just to get some experience with whats involved -- including 
checkpoint recover.  Ask questions here on list if issues.

Yours,
St.Ack




